5
A Star Point Pattern (44)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0\deflang1033\deflangfe1042{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par \b Black to Play.\b0
\par When white invades the corner at 1, black 2 blocks in the right direction.
\par
\par When there a black stone like \'a1\'e3, you should play like this in order to place an emphasis on developing this side.
\par
\par After white 3 and black 4 are exchanged, it might look a little strange for white to extend with 5.
\par
\par How can black respond to this move?
\par }
