Diagram 1 (Which Side to Cut?)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f2\froman\fprq2\fcharset0 Times New Roman;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par First of all, black pushing down between white's stones with 1 to create a weakpoint is the only move.
\par
\par \pard\ltrpar\nowidctlpar\qj The problem is after white defends with 2. black has a hard time deciding which side is better to cut on, \b\f1 A\lang1033\kerning2\f2\fs20  \lang1042\kerning0\b0\f0\fs18 or \b\f1 B\b0\f0 .
\par \pard\ltrpar
\par White side do you think is correct?
\par }
