Diagram 3 (Cutting on the left)
[{\rtf1\fbidis\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\ltrpar\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par What if black cuts on the left side?
\par In this case, white has to connect at 2.
\par
\par Now you can see which side is correct for black to cut on, can't you?
\par
\par Black should not have cut on the right side. The black stone was sacrificed in vain.
\par
\par The sequence in this diagram is correct.
\par }
